 Position Description 
 
 
 The mission of Argonneâ€™s Environmental Science Division (EVS) is to provide pioneering fundamental and multidisciplinary research and innovative analyses to solve global and local challenges, applying our core competency in predictive environmental understanding. Argonne is home to a wide variety of computing systems, including some of the most powerful high-performance computers in the world. These systems provide computing power to advance understanding in a broad range of disciplines. 
The EVS division seeks a post-doctoral appointee to conduct studies on the effects of human activities on terrestrial and/or aquatic ecosystems. The appointee will develop ecological models and statistical approaches to address problems related to ecosystem services, climate change, agricultural systems, and energy-environment interactions. The appointee will report the analysis and conclusions from these studies in environmental impact assessments, journal publications, and other technical reports. Frequently interact with other ecologists and natural resources scientists to develop research designs and prepare publications. Work collaboratively and develop working relationships with DOE and other federal agencies, industry, academia, and NGOs for the purpose of research. Document the results of technical work in the form of reports, journal articles, conference papers, etc. 
 Position Requirements 
 
 
 Recent PhD in ecology, botany, biology or related field. 
Knowledge of animal and/or plant populations and the effects of human activities and/or environmental change on those populations. 
Knowledge of ecological systems and population ecology including terrestrial, aquatic, and/or wetland systems. 
Knowledge of ecological risk assessment techniques and geospatial methods, tools, and techniques to model and analyze ecosystem perturbations. 
Knowledge of ecological and agricultural systems and ecosystem services; understanding of climate issues and adaptations to climate change. 
Data science background with experience with artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning (ML), and/or deep learning (DL) applications in ecology. 
Demonstrate excellent career growth potential, including proposal development. 
Participation in seminars, conferences, and other scientific meetings. 
Ability to model Argonneâ€™s Core Values: Impact, Safety, Respect, Integrity, and Teamwork. 
Preferred skills: 
 
Experience with remote sensing applications in ecology. 
Experience with plant identification and wetland delineation. 
Experience with modern technologies for ecological screening and monitoring, including but not limited to wildlife cameras, acoustic and ultrasonic recorders, and e-DNA applications. 
 As an equal employment opportunity and affirmative action employer, and in accordance with our core values of impact, safety, respect, integrity and teamwork, Argonne National Laboratory is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace that fosters collaborative scientific discovery and innovation. In support of this commitment, Argonne encourages minorities, women, veterans and individuals with disabilities to apply for employment. Argonne considers all qualified applicants for employment without regard to age, ancestry, citizenship status, color, disability, gender, gender identity, gender expression, genetic information, marital status, national origin, pregnancy, race, religion, sexual orientation, veteran status or any other characteristic protected by law.
 
 
Argonne employees, and certain guest researchers and contractors, are subject to particular restrictions related to participation in Foreign Government Sponsored or Affiliated Activities, as defined and detailed in United States Department of Energy Order 486.1A. You will be asked to disclose any such participation in the application phase for review by Argonne's Legal Department.
 
 
All Argonne offers of employment are contingent upon a background check that includes an assessment of criminal conviction history conducted on an individualized and case-by-case basis. Please be advised that Argonne positions require upon hire (or may require in the future) for the individual be to obtain a government access authorization that involves additional background check requirements. Failure to obtain or maintain such government access authorization could result in the withdrawal of a job offer or future termination of employment.
